{'id': 32822276, 'body': 'Hi there, thank you for leaving a review! This is likely due to the size of your backyard pools. Apple Watches have a very hard time recording laps correctly in small pools such as pools shorter than 10meters. 

The best way to get an accurate recording in a small pool is to either follow a guided workout on the watch or to make sure you are not doing any push offs underwater and your wrist is clearly coming out of the water when swimming.

If you have any questions, we are happy to help. Feel free to reach out to support@myswimpro.com', 'modified': '2022-10-27T14:55:50Z'}

{'id': 29341136, 'body': 'Hi there, thank you for leaving us another review. We'd love to help improve your experience in the app. Could you please send us a message at support@myswimpro.com so we can help resolve the issues you've encountered with your workouts and the tracking? 

It sounds like the workouts were not being personalized and so the intervals were not set correctly. If the intervals are set correctly, you shouldn't have to use the "next rep" button nor turning water lock on and off through out the workout. 

Looking forward to hearing from you!', 'modified': '2022-04-22T22:53:05Z'}

{'id': 13718125, 'body': "Thank you for taking the time to leave us a review! We are disappointed to hear that you have been encountering problems with getting your workout to sync to strava.

We are aware of an issue currently that is causing some members to not be able to sync properly with strava and we are working to get this resolved as quickly as possible.

If you send us a message at support@myswimpro.com we'd be happy to help get your trial extended so that you can give the app a proper test with the sync features once it is resolved.", 'modified': '2020-02-26T14:12:52Z'}

{'id': 20936612, 'body': 'Hi there, thank you for leaving us a review. We are disappointed to hear about these issues!

We have not made any changes to free and paid versions in the timeline you listed. Can you please send us a message at support@myswimpro.com so that we get everything working as it should be for you? 
', 'modified': '2021-02-08T19:10:40Z'}

{'id': 13083920, 'body': 'Thank you for taking the time to leave us a review! We are excited to have you in the community!


Once you workout is loaded to your watch, you no longer need the phone at the pool with you!

If you'd rather not bring your phone at all, what you can do is load the workout to your watch at home, then close out of the app. Once you get to the pool, you can use the "last viewed" button on the watch app to load the workout last shown on your watch. This way you no longer need the phone to start your workout once you are at the pool. Please send us a message at support@myswimpro.com if you have any questions!', 'modified': '2020-01-23T15:42:25Z'}

{'id': 25533908, 'body': 'We are disappointed to hear that you are encountering issues!
Can you please send us a message at support@myswimpro.com or use the "contact us" form in the app so we can understand the issues you are encountering and get them resolved?

In addition, we had an update today if you could update the app and give it a try as well, that would help us understand where this issue is coming from for you!', 'modified': '2021-10-06T18:24:30Z'}

{'id': 19051310, 'body': 'Thank you for leaving us a review! What could we improve to help raise your rating from a 2 start to a 5 star?

