{'id': 24899719, 'body': 'Thank you for taking the time to leave us a review. The 5 workouts refers to being able to save up to 5 workouts to your workout library (custom workouts).

 These features are built into the app and are 100% Free Forever: Write and log an unlimited number of workouts. Load an unlimited number of Custom workouts to a compatible smartwatch. Sometimes you just want to log how far you swam and don’t have the time to put in the sets you did. For that, we have Quick Log! Custom workout builder and save up to three workouts to your personal library. Profile to show distance swum. Profile to show workouts logged Monthly challenges! Earn achievements based on distance and number of workouts logged. Global community of fellow swimmers. Inspiring stories delivered to your inbox every week Daily workout ideas, tips, and technique videos available on our blog and social media.
', 'modified': '2021-09-03T21:45:43Z'}

{'id': 40645333, 'body': 'Thank you for taking the time to leave a review.
The initial distance is just your comfortable swimming distance. Once further in, you can set the your preferred metric to be meters. 

In regards to the weight, the team is aware of this issue and working to resolve it! In the meantime, the app will use the setting set from your apple health instead. ', 'modified': '2023-12-12T19:35:27Z'}

{'id': 32623050, 'body': "Hi there, thank you for taking the time to leave us a review. On the free version of the app you can track unlimited unguided swim Workouts with a compatible watch.Z

If you have questions on how to use this feature, don't hesitate to reach out at support@myswimpro.com


", 'modified': '2022-10-17T15:17:49Z'}

{'id': 22661111, 'body': 'Thank you for taking the time to leave us a review. We are disappointed to hear that you had a bad experience. 

It sounds like you were using the "no interval" feature on the guided workouts. Currently on the sets with "no interval" you have to manually advance to the next set/rep when you are done resting, however it will still track a correct split time for you. Soon the No interval feature will be upgraded to move on automatically when you push off for your next rep/set without manually advancing. We'd love to talk more about your experience and get the app working 100% for you. Can you please send us a message at support@myswimpro.com so we can talk further?

', 'modified': '2021-05-06T15:54:36Z'}

